Today's tactics lesson will be the summary of all previously learned tactics.
In the first lesson, we learned about the "use of tempo".
Do you remember what tempo is?
It is not easy to define the tempo in renju.

Perhaps it means, "the threat that forces the opponent follow you, thus giving you the chance to do something on your own"

After that, there was no activity on either sides.
But since it was white's turn to play,
In this case, tempo was needed for white in two reasons:
1. tempo helped to save from loss
2. tempo helped to make white's own win.
But please remember, tempo is not always good or necessary.
When points 1 or 2  is not fulfilled,
gain the tempo when we need it
But some players struggle for tempo even when it is not necessary.
Sometimes the meaningless struggle over the tempo will exhaust your resources
and later, after you get tempo, you have nothing to do with it.
